Chapter 9

Years passed, and Kion's reign as king of the savannah continued. Under his leadership, the pride had grown in size and strength, and Kion was widely respected by all the animals of the savannah.

But as Kion grew older, he began to feel a sense of restlessness. He had accomplished much in his life, but he knew that there was still much to be done. He decided to set out on a journey, to explore new lands and seek out new challenges.
